{"parse":{"title":"Inverse care law","pageid":5152675,"revid":844231428,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>The inverse care law</b> is the principle that the availability of good medical or social care tends to vary inversely with the need of the population served. Proposed by <a href=\"/wiki/Julian_Tudor_Hart\" title=\"Julian Tudor Hart\">Julian Tudor Hart</a> in 1971, the term has since been widely adopted. It is a <a href=\"/wiki/Pun\" title=\"Pun\">pun</a> on <a href=\"/wiki/Inverse-square_law\" title=\"Inverse-square law\">inverse-square law</a>, a term and concept from <a href=\"/wiki/Physics\" title=\"Physics\">physics</a>.\n</p><p>The law states that:\n<i>\"The availability of good medical care tends to vary inversely with the need for it in the population served. This ... operates more completely where medical care is most exposed to market forces, and less so where such exposure is reduced.\"</i> <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Hart later paraphrased his argument: \"To the extent that health care becomes a commodity it becomes distributed just like champagne. That is rich people gets lots of it. Poor people don\u2019t get any of it.\"\n</p><p>The Inverse Care Law is a key issue in the debate about <a href=\"/wiki/Health_inequality\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Health inequality\">health inequality</a>.  As <a href=\"/wiki/Frank_Dobson\" title=\"Frank Dobson\">Frank Dobson</a> put it when he was <a href=\"/wiki/Secretary_of_State_for_Health\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Secretary of State for Health\">Secretary of State for Health</a>: \"Inequality in health is the worst inequality of all. There is no more serious inequality than knowing that you'll die sooner because you're badly off.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Further_reading\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Further reading</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Further_reading\">Further reading</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Inverse_care_law&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Further reading\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><cite class=\"citation journal\"><a href=\"/wiki/Julian_Tudor_Hart\" title=\"Julian Tudor Hart\">Tudor Hart, J.</a> (1971). \"The Inverse Care Law\". <i>The Lancet</i>. <b>297</b>: 405\u2013412. <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//doi.org/10.1016/S0140-6736%2871%2992410-X\">10.1016/S0140-6736(71)92410-X</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Lancet&amp;rft.atitle=The+Inverse+Care+Law&amp;rft.volume=297&amp;rft.pages=405-412&amp;rft.date=1971&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1016%2FS0140-6736%2871%2992410-X&amp;rft.aulast=Tudor+Hart&amp;rft.aufirst=J.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AInverse+care+law\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation journal\">Watt, G. (2002). \"The inverse care law today\". <i>The Lancet</i>. <b>360</b>: 252\u2013254. <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//doi.org/10.1016/S0140-6736%2802%2909466-7\">10.1016/S0140-6736(02)09466-7</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Lancet&amp;rft.atitle=The+inverse+care+law+today&amp;rft.volume=360&amp;rft.pages=252-254&amp;rft.date=2002&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1016%2FS0140-6736%2802%2909466-7&amp;rft.aulast=Watt&amp;rft.aufirst=G.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AInverse+care+law\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.sochealth.co.uk/public-health-and-wellbeing/poverty-and-inequality/the-inverse-care-law/a-reappraisal-of-the-inverse-care-law/\">A Reappraisal of the Inverse Care Law</a> Cooper K., 2010</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Inverse_care_law&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Health_policy\" title=\"Health policy\">Health policy</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Inverse_benefit_law\" title=\"Inverse benefit law\">Inverse benefit law</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Patient_safety\" title=\"Patient safety\">Patient safety</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Public_health\" title=\"Public health\">Public health</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=